										<content:encoded><![CDATA[
<p>life is<br>a puzzle<br>that we are still putting together<br>taking apart<br>and trying to put back together<br>looking for<br>the missing peaces<br>or parts<br>that we just can’t see<br>that don’t fit<br>or don’t belong<br>that shouldn’t be<br>yet make us strong</p>



<p>life is<br>a question<br>that we ask<br>and cannot find<br>the answers yet<br>the whys<br>and hows<br>the whens<br>or wheres<br>and answers<br>that seem just out of reach<br>yet we ask them still<br>each day<br>and hope for answers<br>just out of reach</p>



<p>life is<br>a painting<br>a photo<br>a book we read<br>a movie we watch<br>a conversation we have<br>a story we tell<br>a meal we eat<br>a day we live<br>one day<br>a home<br>a visit<br>a place we leave<br>a place we stay</p>



<p>life is<br>knowing<br>and not knowing<br>laughing<br>crying<br>hoping<br>sharing<br>bearing<br>giving<br>and taking</p>



<p>life is<br>a journey<br>to a place<br>a time<br>a state of being<br>with no reason or rhyme<br>where we hope to be<br>better<br>richer<br>stronger<br>or maybe just smarter<br>than we were today</p>



<p>life is<br>a gift<br>that we open up<br>one day at a time<br>to see what we will get<br>and like it or not<br>we can not return<br>or exchange<br>there’s no receipt<br>and victory<br>or defeat<br>it is what it is</p>



<p>life is<br>the story we tell<br>to others<br>to ourselves<br>of days gone by<br>of days yet to come<br>of fears<br>and hopes<br>of victories<br>yet won<br>of lies<br>and deceit<br>of doubt<br>without reason<br>of good<br>and of bad<br>of brokenness<br>and of sad</p>



<p>life is<br>awake<br>and asleep<br>dreaming<br>daring<br>hoping<br>that tomorrow<br>will be better<br>than yesterday</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
